Breadcrumb

    1. Home

Personal data protection notice

1. ​​​​​​Why a personal data protection notice?

   The purpose of this personal data protection notice is to inform you
   about how your personal data are processed on the
   www.ifp-school.com website (hereafter referred to as “the Website”),
   within the context of application of the General Data Protection
   Regulation (EU 2016/679) and the amended French Data Protection Law of
   6 January 1978.
   This Notice explains which personal data are processed and how they may
   be used.

2. What is meant by personal data?

   Personal data refers to any information relating directly or indirectly
   to an identified or identifiable person. A surname, first name, postal
   or electronic address, a telephone number or an IP address are all
   examples of personal data.
   You can visit the Commission Nationale de l’Informatique et des
   Libertés (CNIL, French Data Protection Authority) website to find out
   more about the exact nature of personal data, the processing of
   personal data  and the broad principles of data protection.

3. Who is responsible for processing the data?

   Your personal data are processed by a legal entity, IFP Energies
   nouvelles (IFPEN), a French State-owned industrial and commercial
   establishment, sis 1 et 4, avenue de Bois-Préau, 92852 Rueil-Malmaison
   Cedex. IFPEN is the data controller, i.e., it is the body that defines
   the objectives and procedures for processing your personal data.

4. When are your data collected?

   Depending on how you interact with IFPEN, the latter may collect your
   personal data as described below.
   Your personal data are collected:
     * When you browse the Website, via cookies placed on your computer;

     * When you complete and send back the form present on the Website
       (subscription to newsletters, subscription to events, etc.). Fields
       on the form marked with an asterisk are required and must be
       completed for the request to be processed correctly. If they are
       not completed, IFPEN will be unable to respond to your request.

5. In what ways do we use your personal data?

   You will be informed about what IFPEN does with your personal data at
   the time they are collected.
   The personal data collected when you use the Website enable us to:
     * manage your subscription to newsletters;
     * manage your subscription to organized events;
     * follow up requests made via the Website’s contact page;
     * take into account notifications relating to changes to the Website
       you may have requested (preferred themes, notification frequency
       and changes made).

6. Who has access to your personal data?

   The personal data collected by IFPEN are for the exclusive use, within
   their competence, of IFPEN’s internal departments responsible for
   Website communication and management, as well as its subcontractors,
   within the context of the execution of services associated with the use
   of the Website and the management of communications sent by IFPEN
   (communication agencies, routing service providers).

7. How long are your personal data kept for?

   Your personal data are kept for the period necessary to fulfill the
   purposes described.
   You will be informed about how long they will be kept at the time they
   are collected or when you first enter into contact with IFPEN.

8. What rights do you have regarding your data?

   In accordance with the regulations applicable and under the conditions
   defined within them, you can, at any time, exercise your:
     * Right to access: you can ask IFPEN for information concerning the
       processing of your personal data and a copy of the aforementioned
       data.
     * Right to rectification: you can request the rectification of
       inaccurate personal data when data held by IFPEN are incorrect or
       incomplete.
     * Right to erasure: you have the right to ask IFPEN to erase your
       personal data when one of the reasons specified by the regulations
       exists (redundancy of the data, withdrawal of your consent for
       processing based on the latter, etc.).
     * Right to object: you have the right to object to the processing of
       your data at any time.
     * Right to portability of your personal data: you have the right to
       receive your personal data in a readable format.
     * Right to restriction: you may ask IFPEN to suspend the processing
       of your personal data when one of the reasons specified by the
       regulations exists (data accuracy challenged, etc.).
     * Within the framework of the conditions defined by the regulations,
       you also have the right to define general or specific directives
       relating to the use of your personal data following your death.

   When your personal data are processed with your consent, you may
   withdraw this consent at any time. However, you are informed that any
   processing carried out prior to this withdrawal of consent will remain
   valid.

9. How can your exercise your rights?

   You can exercise your rights by contacting our Data Protection Officer,
   with proof of your identity, via:
   - email to DPO@ifpen.fr
   - post to IFP Energies nouvelles – Déléguée à la protection des données
   (Data Protection Officer) - 1 et 4, avenue de Bois-Préau, 92852 -
   Rueil-Malmaison Cedex

   You may, at any time, request that no further communications be sent by
   IFPEN, by clicking on the subscription cancellation link present with
   each communication.

   IFPEN makes every effort to protect your personal data. However, should
   you consider that their processing breaches your rights or that your
   request has not be satisfied, you may submit a complaint to the French
   Data Protection Authority (CNIL).

10. What cookies are used on the Website?

   IFPEN uses different cookies on the Website to improve its
   interactivity and its features. Session cookies are required to ensure
   the Website operates correctly. Such cookies are deleted when you close
   your browser.
   Other cookies placed on your computer with your prior consent are also
   used, namely:
     * Audience measurement cookies are used by the Website to compile a
       range of statistics (number of visits, number of pages viewed,
       internet user activity on the Website);
     * Cookies to enable multimedia content on the Website (videos) to be
       viewed;

   When you visit the Website for the first time, a banner informs you of
   the presence of these cookies and asks you to specify your choice. They
   are only placed on your computer if you accept them or if you continue
   to browse by visiting a second page of the Website. You can find out
   about cookies and adjust your settings to either accept or block them
   at any time.

MANAGING COOKIES

   For Mozilla firefox :
   1. Select the “Tools” menu then “Options”;
   2. Click the “Privacy” panel;
   3. Go to the "cookies" menu and select the options you want.

   For Microsoft Internet Explorer :
   1. Select the "Tools” menu, followed by "Internet Options";
   2. Click "Confidentiality";
   3. Select desired level using the cursor.

   For Google Chrome :
   1. Click the icon depicting 3 horizontal lines at the top right of the
   screen and select “settings”;
   2. Click “advanced settings”;
   3. Under “confidentiality”, click “content settings”;
   4. Check the “block cookies” box .

   Personal data collected using cookies are kept for a period of thirteen
   (13) months from the time of your first visit to the Website.

11. Modification of the Personal Data Protection Notice

   IFPEN reserves the right to modify or, more generally, update the
   general provisions of the current Notice at any time and without prior
   warning. You are therefore invited to consult it regularly.

   > Legal Notices

   logo Ifp School
   The school for energy innovation and sustainable mobility

   IFP School offers applied graduate programs, providing students and
   young professionals from all over the world with education in the
   fields of energy which meets the needs of industry and the demands of
   society with particular emphasis on sustainable development and
   innovation.

